name: lib/cube.js
fromSerialization
description: Create a cube from the result of the serialize() method.

params.name: obj
params.description: Object retrieved by calling the serialize method on a Cube instance.

name: constructor
description: Build a cube from it's components

params.name: id
params.description: A unique identifier for this cube across the application.

params.name: dimensions
params.description: The list of dimensions that this cube is using

params.name: dimensionGroups
params.description: The list of dimension groups that this cube is using

params.name: data
params.description: Data contained in the cube. The size of this array must be the product of the number of elements in the dimension.

name: query
description: Query this cube splitting the result by the provided dimension ids and filters.

params.name: filter
params.description: Elements that should be included by dimension. Missing dimensions are not filtered.

params.name: withTotals
params.description: Include an additional "total" key at every level

return.description: An nested object which contain total value in each dimensionElement.

name: _query_total
description: Retrieve the total value matching a given filter.

params.name: filter
params.description: Elements that should be included by dimension. Missing dimensions are not filtered.

return.description: total value matching the provided filter.

name: _query_rec
description: Retrieve the total value matching given indexes and read offset.
examples:
var c = new Cube('sells', [time, location], [], [0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]);
c._query_rec([], 0); // 0
c._query_rec([], 2); // 2

c._query_rec([[1, 2]], 0); // 3
c._query_rec([[0], [0]], 5); // 5
todo: Would be faster to use push/pop instead of shift/unshift into the indexes.

params.name: offset
params.description: Offset when reading from the data (used to recurse).

return.description: Total value extracted from the cube.

name: _remove_dimension_groups
description:
When querying the cube with _query_total(), we only support
using dimensions (and not dimensionGroups).

This rewrites any filter so that they use dimensions.

name: CubeCollection
description:
A cube collection is a container that contains all cubes from the variables of a given project

If there is a need to implement queries across multiple cubes, it can be implemented here.

name: lib/dimension-group.js
DimensionGroup
description:
A DimensionGroup allows to query cubes on dimension aggregates.
For instance, for a cube containing a "date" dimension, then a "month" dimension group can be created.

name: lib/dimension.js
lib/index.js
lib/time-slot.js
TimeSlot
description:
A class representing a time slot used in monitoring.
This can be a given day, epidemiological week, month, quarter, ...

name: fromDate

params.name: utcDate
params.description: Date which we want to build the TimeSlot around

params.name: periodicity
params.description: One of day, week_sat, week_sun, week_mon, month, quarter, semester, year

return.description: The TimeSlot instance of the given periodicity containing utcDate

name: _getEpidemiologicWeekEpoch
description: Get the date from which we should count weeks to compute the epidemiological week number.
todo:
This function is incredibly verbose for what it does.
Probably a single divmod could give the same result but debugging was nightmarish.

name: constructor
description:
Constructs a TimeSlot instance from a time slot value.
The periodicity will be automatically computed.

params.name: value
params.description: A valid TimeSlot value (those can be found calling the `value` getter).

name: value
description:
The value of the TimeSlot.
This is a string that uniquely identifies this timeslot.

For instance: `2010`, `2010-Q1`, `2010-W07-sat`.

name: periodicity
description:
The periodicity used for this timeslot.
By periodicity, we mean, the method that was used to cut time into slots.

For instance: `year`, `quarter`, `week-sat`, ...

name: firstDate
description: The date where this instance of TimeSlot begins.

name: lastDate
description: The date where this instance of TimeSlot ends.

name: toUpperSlot
description: Creates a TimeSlot instance with a longer periodicity that contains this one.

name: next
description: Creates a TimeSlot instance of the same periodicity than the current once, but which follows it
